The focal point for tobacco control is Dr Andrea Yearwood Director Health Policy Research and Planning at the Ministry of Health.
Our current mechanism for national coordination is the National Tobacco Control Committee (NTCC) and the Focal Point. This Committee is multisectoral and the Chairperson is Dr Yearwood who is also the Focal Point. 
The Terms of Reference of the NTCC are to:
1. develop a National Tobacco Control Plan for Trinidad and Tobago with the aim of preventing and reducing tobacco consumption nicotine addiction and exposure to tobacco smoke;
2. co-ordinate national implementation of the Tobacco Control Plan paying particular attention to the deadlines for implementation as imposed by the Framework Convention;
3. monitor evaluate and update the strategies identified in the National Plan as necessary;
4. develop and co-ordinate the implementation of policies other plans and programmes that may be necessary for Trinidad and Tobago to meet all of its obligations under the Framework Convention on Tobacco Control;
5. monitor Trinidad and Tobagos progress in implementing the Framework Convention
6. prepare periodic reports on implementation as may be required under Article 21 of the Framework Convention; and
7. hold at least six (6) meetings per year or more regularly as may be deemed necessary.
The Committee comprises persons from the following departments of Health: Health Policy Research and Planning;	Health Promotion and Public Health; Legal; Communication; and the National Oncology Programme.
The Committee also comprises person from other Ministries/Agencies such as the Ministry of the Attorney General the Ministry of Sport and Youth Affairs the Ministry of Finance (Customs and Excise Division) the Ministry of Trade and Industry the Ministry of Social Development the Trinidad and Tobago Cancer Society Coalition for a Tobacco-Free Trinidad and Tobago South Cancer Support Network and a representative physician
Additional persons with the necessary skills and expertise are co-opted as required.
